headline.main: Advice for Physicians; Most Private Practitioners Neglect Care of Themselves, Study Reveals

byline.original: By HOWARD A. RUSK, M. D

docs.abstract: Dr Rusk on USSR Dr Gurevich views on coronary ills in capitalist nations
docs.lead_paragraph: The old adage that the "shoemaker's children go barefoot" is particularly applicable to physicians and their own health. It is a case of "Don't do as I do, but do as I tell you."
